            "body": "If you change\n\n```lua\nvim.schedule(function()\n  vim.opt.guicursor = guicursor_saved\nend)\n```\n\nto simply `vim.opt.guicursor = guicursor_saved` then the issue no longer reproduces.\n\nThis is what's happening:\n\n1. On `:term`, the `BufLeave` autocommand fires, and schedules the change to `'guicursor'`\n2. Before that change occurs, the `terminal_enter` function is called. This function saves the existing value of the terminal cursor in `'guicursor'` so that it can be restored when Terminal mode ends. At this point, `'guicursor'` hasn't been changed yet, so it still has `a:CursorTransparent/lCursor`. That is the value that gets saved\n3. While Terminal mode is active, `'guicursor'` is modified\n4. When Terminal mode ends (`<C-\\><C-N>`) the saved terminal cursor value is restored (and so is assigned the `CursorTransparent` highlight group again)\n5. When you re-enter terminal mode, the `CursorTransparent` highlight group is applied\n\nIf you remove the `vim.schedule` then the `'guicursor'` option is changed before step (2) above.\n\nStill need to find the proper fix to prevent this from happening when vim.schedule is used.",
